main event: On September 25, 1952, two unidentified aerial objects were observed by a civilian and an airman over Offutt Air Force Base in Omaha, Nebraska.
interesting points: The objects were described as bright white or silver and were in a straight line formation,The sighting lasted approximately 3-4 minutes before the objects disappeared,The observer reported seeing both moving and stationary objects,The report indicates the phenomenon was corroborated by radar observations,No photographs were present in the document.
witness description: one airman of the 25th Air Division, USAF, and one civilian
